<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911118-0124</DOCNO><DOCID>911118-0124.</DOCID><HL>   MECA Software Inc.   Agrees to Purchase   Of Live Free or Die</HL><DATE>11/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10D</SO><CO>   MECA</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- MECA Software Inc. said it agreed tobuy Live Free or Die Software Ltd. for at least $5.8 millionin cash, notes and MECA common stock.   A MECA spokesman declined to disclose how much Live Freeor Die shareholders would receive in cash or stock as part ofthe agreement. But the company said if Live Free or Die'srevenue hits a certain level next year, shareholders wouldreceive an additional undisclosed payout.</LP><TEXT>   Live Free or Die is the holding company for Great AmericanSoftware, a Nashua, N.H., company that develops, markets andsupports small business accounting software systems andrelated products.   MECA's president and chief executive officer, Daniel M.Schley, said that Great American Software, with its&quot;One-Write Plus&quot; accounting system, has successfully targetedthe market MECA seeks to tap. In the fiscal year ended July31, Great American had revenue of about $8 million. Aspokesman for MECA declined to disclose the company'searnings but said it was profitable in fiscal 1991.   Fairfield-based MECA Software develops, publishes andmarkets a family of personal and business productivitysoftware. The company's products include Andrew Tobias'sManaging Your Money, TaxCut, Home Lawyer and the Manager'sOrganizer.</TEXT></DOC>